==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Succedaneum
<hw>Suc`ce*da"ne*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Succedanea</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[NL. See
<er>Succedaneous</er>.]</ety> <def>One who, or that which, succeeds to
the place of another; that which is used for something else; a
substitute;</def> <specif>specifically</specif> <fld>(Med.)</fld>,
<def>a remedy used as a substitute for another.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In lieu of me, you will have a very charming
<qex>succedaneum</qex>, Lady Harriet Stanhope.</q>
<rj><qau>Walpole.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Succeed</ent>⟦br⟧
